Scene 1 — Multiple fire instances (graded hazard)
Image prompt

Suburban street. A car is fully engulfed in flames (large fire). Nearby, a small trash fire burns by the curb. Several houses are close. A person stands at a distance watching. Daytime.

Caption

“A car is on fire near houses, and a smaller fire is burning nearby. A person stands at a distance watching.”

Objects present (intended)

car, fire (large), fire (small), house, person, street, trash pile

What it tests

Causal prioritization (dominant vs secondary hazard)

Graded hazard updating (hazard decreases but not to zero)

Instance grounding (correct category, wrong instance)

Expected causal behavior

Suppression variable: dominant fire (car fire)

After visual suppression:

Hazard drops but remains > 0 (small fire still present)

Recommendations downgrade (e.g., evacuate may drop; monitor/secure may remain)

CEE failure modes exposed

Instance grounding failure (wrong fire/car instance suppressed → low CES_visual)

Over-binary hazard collapse (hazard incorrectly goes to 0)

Causal Form Mimicry (high structure/semantics but failed intervention)




A house on fire in a neighborhood at night and a car is parked nearby

